radiographic_examinations.findings: Tiny bilateral pleural effusions with bibasilar atelectasis in the visualized lung base. Liver is normal without focal lesions or evidence of intrahepatic biliary dilatation. Two small gallstones in a non-distended gallbladder without evidence of acute cholecystitis. Kidneys appear atrophic bilaterally with a known cystic structure. Suspicious small renal lesion in the right interpolar region without any short interval changes. Metallic stent in the pancreas with interval development of fat stranding along the CDB in the porta hepatis, measuring approximately 4 x 3cm.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: No short interval changes noted in the suspicious small renal lesion. Fat stranding area noted in current examination showing interval development.
